<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1480,1842]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,338,1480,1506]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 10.0-11.0 mm. 
<taxonomicName box="[747,1004,1480,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Argillophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcilla">
<emphasis box="[747,1004,1480,1505]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Argillophora furcilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive species with cream forewings speckled with black scales and an angular white band in the middle of the wing that is bordered by darker linear patches, with small black dots along outer margin. 
<collectingCountry box="[904,963,1554,1580]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing is white to pale gray that becomes darker at wing margin.
</paragraph>
